Anadolu Hayat Emeklilik AS (ANHYT) ,
Turkeyâ€™s biggest private pensions company, jumped the most in
more than two months after first-quarter profit rose 57 percent,
beating estimates.  The shares gained 3.5 percent to 4.17 liras at the close in
Istanbul, the biggest increase since Feb. 16.  Net income rose to 21.3 million liras ($12 million) from
13.6 million liras in the first quarter of 2011, Anadolu Hayat
said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  today.  The company was expected to earn 19 million liras,
according to the average of three analyst estimates compiled by
